description: TIE ("Twin Ionic Engine") Fighters are the most common starfighter used by the Galactic Empire in space battles. They are known for the shriek they leave behind as they fly quickly through space and atmospheres and are equipped for laser cannons.

name: Blast Shield Helmet
description: Helmet used by Luke Skywalker during his training with Ben Kenobi to learn about lightsabers and The Force. Unable to see anything around him, Luke must rely on his other senses to use his lightsaber and help him avoid being hit by the training droid.

name: Training Remote Droid
description: Used by Ben Kenobi to teach Luke Skywalker how to use a lightsaber and The Force.

name: E-11 Blaster Rifle
description: Most commonly used blaster rifle by the Imperial Stormtroopers. Not known for their accuracy, they can still hurt or kill people who are hit by their energy blasts.

name: Pot
description: A container typically used for cooking or holding liquids or other substances.

name: Wooden Spoon
description: A kitchen utensil commonly used for stirring

name: Bagpipes
description: A musical instrument consisting of a bag, usually made of leather or synthetic materials, and several pipes. The bag is inflated by the player either blowing into it or using a bellows, and air is then released into the pipes, producing sound.

name: Banjo
description: A stringed musical instrument with a round body and a long neck, usually featuring five strings.

name: Pumpkin
description: A type of squash plant known for its large, round fruit with a thick, orange or yellow outer skin.

name: Salt
description: Salt is a crystalline mineral substance composed mainly of sodium chloride (NaCl).

name: Ticket
description: A piece of paper or small card that gives the holder a certain right, especially to enter a place, travel by public transport, or participate in an even

name: City Lights
description: Generally refers to the artificial illumination found in urban areas, typically at night.

name: house
description: A building for human habitation, especially one that is lived in by a family or small group of people

name: White dress
description: A dress, many times formal dress, often long and white, worn by a woman at her wedding

name: Pebbles
description: A small stone made smooth and round by the action of water or sand

name: The Lightning Bolt
description: The Lightning Bolt is the powerful and iconic weapon of Zeus, the king of the gods in Greek mythology. In "Percy Jackson & the Olympians: The Lightning Thief," the Lightning Bolt serves as a central plot device. Its theft sets off the main conflict of the story, as Percy Jackson, the protagonist, embarks on a quest to retrieve it and prevent a war among the gods. As a symbol of Zeus' authority and power, the Lightning Bolt is highly sought after and feared by both mortals and immortals alike. Its significance extends beyond its physical properties, representing the balance of power and the potential consequences of its misuse. Throughout the story, the Lightning Bolt serves as a catalyst for Percy's journey, driving the narrative forward and shaping the events that unfold.

name: Riptide
description: Riptide, also known as Anaklusmos, is the celestial bronze sword wielded by Percy Jackson, the protagonist of the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series. Given to Percy by his mentor, Chiron, Riptide is a powerful weapon with the ability to harm monsters and creatures of the supernatural world. What makes Riptide unique is its ability to transform from a seemingly ordinary ballpoint pen into a deadly sword when uncapped by its rightful owner. This concealment allows Percy to carry it discreetly, making it a valuable asset in his battles against monsters and adversaries. Riptide becomes an essential tool in Percy's quest as he navigates the challenges of being a demigod and confronts the dangers of the mythological world.

name: The Master Bolt
description: The Master Bolt is a potent weapon belonging to Zeus, the king of the gods in Greek mythology. In "Percy Jackson & the Olympians: The Lightning Thief," the Master Bolt serves as a focal point of the plot. This lightning bolt is not just any ordinary bolt of lightning; it is the symbol of Zeus' power and authority over the skies and the natural elements. The Master Bolt possesses immense destructive capabilities, capable of unleashing devastating storms and wreaking havoc upon the world.

name: Golden Drachma
description: The Golden Drachma is a significant item in the world of "Percy Jackson & the Olympians." In Greek mythology and the series, a drachma is a form of currency, but the Golden Drachma holds a special importance for demigods. It's a gold coin that demigods can use to pay for passage on the River Styx or to send Iris Messages to communicate with the gods.

name: Helm of Darkness
description: The Helm of Darkness, also known as the Cap of Invisibility, is a powerful magical artifact belonging to Hades, the god of the underworld, in Greek mythology. In Rick Riordan's "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series, the Helm of Darkness serves as a significant item. The Helm has the ability to render its wearer invisible, allowing them to move unseen by mortal or immortal eyes. This invisibility extends not only to the physical form but also to any objects or creatures the wearer may be carrying or accompanied by.

name: Knee
description: The joint between the thigh and the lower leg in humans:

name: Ball gown
description: A ball gown, ballgown or gown is a type of evening gown worn to a ball or a formal event.

name: Scarlet letter
description: A scarlet A worn as a punitive mark of adultery.

name: Shield of Perseus
description: The shield is a highly reflective surface, crafted from polished bronze or another reflective material. Its most notable feature is its ability to mirror and reflect the image of whatever or whoever stands before it. This unique property allows the shield's wielder to use it defensively, deflecting attacks by reflecting them back to their source.

name: sea anenome
description: Sea anemone's are an ocean dwelling creature with  a tube-shaped body and tentacles around its mouth. These tentacles have tiny stingers to catch food and protect themselves. Sea anemones can be small or big and come in many bright colors like red, orange, or green. They stick to rocks or the ocean floor and stay still while their tentacles sway in the water.

name: Starfish
description: A starfish is a sea creature that lives in the ocean. It has a shape like a star with five arms. Starfish come in different sizes and colors, and they can be found in oceans all around the world. They live on the ocean floor and use their arms to move around and catch food. Starfish are known for their ability to regenerate lost arms, which means they can grow back if they lose one.

name: Coral
description: Coral is a tiny sea animal that lives together in large groups called colonies. They build hard skeletons from calcium carbonate, forming structures like reefs in warm, shallow oceans. Coral colonies come in many colors and shapes, providing homes for numerous marine creatures.

name: Snail
description: A sea snail is a type of mollusk that lives in the ocean. It has a spiral-shaped shell that it carries on its back for protection. Sea snails come in various sizes and colors and can be found in oceans worldwide. They move by gliding along on a muscular foot and use a rasping tongue, called a radula, to scrape algae and other food from rocks or other surfaces.

name: Sea Urchin
description: A sea urchin is a small, spiny sea creature found in oceans around the world. It has a round body covered in sharp spines and a hard shell-like structure called a test. Sea urchins come in various colors, including black, purple, and red.

name: Seaweed
description: Seaweed is a type of marine plant that grows in the ocean. It comes in many different shapes, sizes, and colors, ranging from small, thread-like strands to large, leafy structures. Seaweed attaches itself to rocks or other surfaces underwater and absorbs nutrients from the surrounding water through its leaves or blades.

name: Lanternfish
description: A lanternfish is a small, deep-sea fish known for their bioluminescent properties, which they use for communication, camouflage, and attracting prey. Lanternfish typically have elongated bodies and large eyes, allowing them to navigate in the dark depths of the ocean.

name: Jug
description: A container typically used for holding and pouring liquids. It usually has a handle for easy carrying and a spout for controlled pouring.

name: Grass
description: Grass is a type of plant that grows in many places, like lawns, fields, and meadows. It has long, slender leaves that are usually green, but can sometimes have shades of yellow, brown, or purple. Grass is often soft to the touch and grows close to the ground in dense patches or tufts.

name: Egg
description: A small, oval-shaped object laid by female birds, reptiles, fish, and some other animals. It serves as a protective structure for the developing embryo inside.

name: Grain
description: Grain refers to the seeds of cereal plants that are cultivated for food. These seeds are small, hard, and typically come in various shapes, colors, and sizes.

name: AC-8 Autocannon
description: The AC-8 Autocannon is one of the stratagems available to the player at Level 10, costing 7,000 Requisition Slips. It is highly effective against bots and can be used as an automatic Railgun with increased versatility and less potential damage and accuracy.

name: APW-1 Anti-Materiel Rifle
description: The APW-1 Anti-Material Rifle is an early game semi-automatic supply Stratagem. It is available at level 2 for 5000 R. You can adjust the zoom level of the scope to 50 meters, 100m and 200m.

name: AR-23 Liberator
description: The AR-23 Liberator is the standard dispenser of democracy in Helldivers 2. Filling the primary weapon slot, it is a light armor-penetrating weapon with three modes: auto, burst, and semi-automatic. It is also equipped with a flashlight, with three modes: auto (which activates the flashlight only in low light conditions), on, and off. It is unlocked upon character creation and automatically equipped. Two variants of the weapon are available for unlock, the AR-23P Liberator Penetrator and AR-23C Liberator Concussive.

name: ARC-12 Blitzer
description: An arc-type shotgun that doesn't need any ammo, and can link electricity between foes.

name: ARC-3 Arc Thrower
description: Projects an arc of lightning at close range. Charges up to project bolts, and may discharge through multiple targets. The ARC-3 Arc Thrower is one of the stratagems available to the player.

name: EAT-17 Expendable Anti-Tank
description: Calls down two EAT-17 expendable anti-tank weapons. The EAT is a one-use rocket capable of damaging heavily armored targets.

name: FAF-14 Spear
description: An anti-tank homing missile which must lock onto its target before launch. Effective against large and armored enemies. The FAF-14 Spear is one of the stratagems available to the player at Level 20.

name: FLAM-40 "Incinerator" Flamethrower
description: A compact flamethrower capable of projecting Napalm flames several meters. Enemies hit with this weapon will start to burn. The flames can ignite fellow Helldivers as well. In Helldivers 2, the Flamethrower is unlocked at Level 10 and is purchasable with 6000 Requisition points.

name: GR-8 Recoilless Rifle
description: A recoilless rifle effective against vehicle armor. Includes support backpack required for reloading. The GR-8 recoilless rifle is one of the stratagems available to the player.

name: JAR-5 Dominator
description: The JAR-5 Dominator is a unique weapon firing two-stage, jet-propelled ammunition that explodes upon entering a target. Capable of medium armor penetration, the Dominator excels at defeating larger, moderately-armored foes such as Hive Guards and Devastators, but struggles against groups of enemy fodder due to high recoil, low rate of fire, and limited ammo capacity.

name: LAS-16 Sickle
description: The LAS-16 Sickle is a laser weapon in Helldivers 2, firing momentary beam pulses in rapid succession after a short charge-up period. Effectively a laser assault rifle, like all laser weapons the Sickle forgoes the need for ammunition in exchange for building up heat, which can be dissipated by simply letting off the trigger. If heat buildup exceeds a certain threshold, however, the weapon will eject its heat sink and the user will be required to load in another before the weapon can be fired again.

name: LAS-5 Scythe
description: The LAS-5 Scythe is an energy weapon in Helldivers‎ 2, firing a continuous, concentrated laser beam that deals damage over time. Like all laser weapons, the Scythe builds up heat rather than consuming ammunition, though maxing out the heat capacity will require the user to exchange the weapon's heat sink.

name: LAS-98 Laser Cannon
description: This cannon is built on upscaled, weaponized laser technology. It fires a heavy, continuous laser beam that consumes no ammunition unless it overheats. The weapon needs to be loaded with emergency heat dump canisters to fire.

name: LAS-99 Quasar Cannon
description: Charges to fire a powerful, explosive energy burst. Has a long cooldown period after firing. The LAS-99 Quasar Cannon is one of the stratagems available to the player.

name: M-105 Stalwart
description: The Stalwart is a support weapon specializing in disposing of large amounts of unarmored targets. Being a sidegrade to the MG-43 Machine Gun it sacrifices individual bullet damage and medium armor penetration for a higher rate of fire, a larger ammo pool, and the ability to reload on the move.

name: MG-206 Heavy Machine Gun
description: A very powerful but difficult-to-wield machine gun with intense recoil. The MG-206 Heavy Machine Gun is one of the stratagems available to the player.

name: MG-43 Machine Gun
description: The MG-43 Machine Gun is an air-cooled, belt-fed general-purpose machine gun in Helldivers 2, and the first stratagem available to the player. It is automatically unlocked after the tutorial mission.

name: P-19 Redeemer
description: A fully-automatic pistol with an extremely high fire rate, allowing for efficient crowd control.

name: P-2 Peacemaker
description: The SEAF standard pistol - offering a high fire rate, generous capacity, and fast reloading.

name: P-4 Senator
description: A high-damage revolver, which can be reloaded with single rounds. A heavy-hitting and reliable sidearm.

name: R-63 Diligence
description: This high-caliber marksman rifle trades magazine capacity and rate of fire for powerful, accurate shots.

name: R-63CS Diligence Counter Sniper
description: A modified Diligence rifle offering increased damage, but a reduced rate of fire. Fires a single bullet at a time.

name: RS-422 Railgun
description: An experimental weapon that prioritizes armor penetration. Must be charged between shots - so choose targets carefully. The RS-422 Railgun is one of the stratagems available to the player at Level 20.

name: SG-225 Breaker
description: A fully automatic shotgun with a high rate of fire, excellent for controlling crowds. Requires frequent reloading.

name: SG-8 Punisher
description: A powerful dual magazine pump-action shotgun, with limited armor penetration. Ideal for small and fast targets.

name: SG-8S Slugger
description: A modified Punisher shotgun firing heavy, high-damage slug rounds. Perfect for punching holes in big targets.

name: AX/LAS-5 "Guard Dog" Rover
description: The role of the Guard Dog Rover is to assist in clearing the lightly armored units taking up your backpack slot. Its effectiveness is limited to lightly armored targets or weak spots.

name: Eagle 500kg Bomb
description: A large bomb obliterating almost any target close to impact. Make sure to clear the area. The Eagle 500kg Bomb is one of the stratagems available to the player at Level 15 for 10,000 requisition slips.

name: EXO-45 Patriot Exosuit
description: The EXO-45 Patriot Exosuit is equipped with fourteen rockets and a mini-gun capable of holding a thousand rounds of ammunition.

name: Eagle Fighter
description: The Eagle's ordnance payload is modular and can include a variety of direct fire cannons, guided missiles, or various guided bombs. However, loiter duration, flight performance envelope, and rearming time can vary significantly depending on the type of weapon load delivered to the target area.

name: LIFT-850 Jump Pack
description: The Helldiver-issued jump pack propels the wearer a short distance into the air and forward, allowing for swift movement over difficult terrain.

name: NUX-223 Hellbomb
description: The Hellbomb is provided when the Helldivers need to destroy a stationary target.

name: Orbital 380MM HE Barrage
description: The Orbital 380mm HE Barrage is an Offensive Orbital Strategem. Effectively a larger variant of the 120mm HE Barrage, this Strategem is excellent for crowd control.

name: Reinforce
description: When a player dies, this stratagem is used to respawn them.

name: Resupply
description: A pod containing ammunition and ordnance. The supplies take some time to deploy as they have to be customized before being deployed.

name: B-1 Supply Pack
description: Supply boxes containing ammunition, with a backpack that allows the user to distribute boxes to fellow Helldivers.
